\intbl \ql \b Background\b0 \line The Independent Institute of Education \'28Pty\'29 Ltd is registered with the Department of Higher Education and Training as a private higher education institution and is accredited to offer higher education programmes by the HEQC.  The institution is currently offering a Certificate in Construction and Engineering Drafting. The institution has also applied for a Higher Certificate in Architectural and Construction Drafting.\line The Advanced Certificate in Architectural and Construction Drafting  programme served at the AC Meeting of 24 March 2011 and it was decided not to accredit for the following reasons\'3A\line 1.No evidence has been presented that the programme is in line with the vision and mission of the institution.\line 2. It is not explicit whether the institutional planning and resource allocation has allowed for the development of the proposed programme.\line 3. The possible articulation mentioned i.e. to B Architecture Degrees at public universities is not substantiated.\line 4. The programme is designed to offer a broad range of modules that are relevant to the drafting profession\'3B however none of the modules are architecture specific.\line 5. Based on the submission it would appear that there are currently no full- time academic staff employed for this programme.\line 6. A certain number of sites listed do not have any staff with qualifications in Architecture.\line 7. The workload allocation model is not aligned to the needs of a programme of this nature. A ratio of 1\'3A40 to 1\'3A55 is not conducive to learning in Architecture.\line 8. The required drafting equipment available to teach such an entry level qualification is not indicated\line \line The institution submitted a representation. \cell \pard 

